    "recap_headline": "University of Georgia Athletics",
    "recap_text": "ATHENS \u2013\nThe eighth-ranked Georgia baseball team completed a four-game sweep over Queens with a 13-3 seven-inning series finale on Sunday afternoon at Foley Field.\nFast Facts\nMatt Scott\n(2-0) got the start on the bump on a staff afternoon for the Bulldogs, providing 2.0 innings while allowing two runs with four strikeouts for the win. Redshirt-junior\nCaleb Jameson\nrelieved Scott in the second and tossed one inning of no-hit ball, striking out all three batters faced.\nGeorgia (15-3) opened scoring in the bottom of the first inning as junior\nDaniel Jackson\n(3-5, 6 RBI, 2 HR) tallied his third home run of the series with a two-run shot to right field.\nQueens (4-12) answered with a two-run home run of their own in the second to tie the score 2-2. The Bulldogs regained the lead in the bottom of the frame off an RBI single from junior\nTre Phelps\n.\nIn the bottom of the third, senior\nKolby Branch\n(1-2, RBI, HR) hit his fourth home run of the series, his eighth of the season. Senior\nBrennan Hudson\n(1-3, 2 RBI, HR)\u00a0followed suit with this third home run of the season, marking his 10\nth\nof the season, to give Georgia a 5-2 lead.\nAfter a scoreless fourth inning, sophomore\nHenry Allen\n(1-4, 3 RBI, HR) smashed a three-run long ball to left field to boost Georgia's lead 8-2.\nThe Royals added another run in the seventh off a solo home run to cut the Bulldogs' lead to five, 8-3.\nFive-straight walks in the bottom of the seventh provided two runs and bases loaded for Jackson. The junior blasted his second grand slam of the week to invoke the 10-run rule and secure the series sweep.\nJackson leads the nation with 14 home runs, and the Bulldogs lead the country with 61 home runs.\nQuotes\nIke Cousins Head Baseball Coach\nWes Johnson\nOn where the team is at this point in the season...\n\"We just finished 11 games in 12 days. Obviously, by design. We're on spring break, so the guys will get a full day off tomorrow. I really like where we're at. That's why I scheduled it that way. You want to find out a lot about your team. I think we have. I think we know what most of the pieces are that we need to put in place. Not only at the mound, but at the plate. Defensively, I really think we've got a lot of options there as well. You're as ready as you can get going into conference play.\"\n#9\nKolby Branch\n| Sr. | INF\nOn today's game...\n\"Everybody's killing it. You look at the scoreboard, just homer after homer, a ton of RBIs, moving the ball around. Doing a good job of that right now.\"\nOn preparing for the start of SEC play next weekend...\n\"You got to take it one day at a time. Take your rest days. It's been a long \u2014 I don't know how long \u2014 14 days, but we've played a ton. You got to take your off days.\"\nUp Next\nGeorgia will return to action for SEC Opening Weekend to host No. 17 Tennessee. First pitch on Friday is set for 6 p.m. The game will be live on SEC Network+ and the Georgia Bulldog Sports Network."
  },
